      "note": "The noun kifl is derived from the root-verb kafala, \"he made himself responsible (for a thing)\". Tabari explains it in this context as denoting \"a share in the responsibility and the sin\". The expression minha (\"out of it\") indicates the part played by the transgressor in the evil enterprise, to which the pronoun ha (\"it\") refers."
